le="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of Bristol enabling them to feel safe and confident to cycle.  However, cycle training is not widely</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> available and is dependent on the priorities of local government. We believe the provision of low-cost high quality adult cycle training should be universally available to adults, wherever they live in England.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Employers should be incentivised to encou</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rage staff who cycle to take up opportunities for training. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.51pt; padding-left:4.49pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Driver awareness training</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As part of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">standard driving test, and the HGV licence test, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">we believe that all drivers should be given cyclist aw</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reness training. This needs to increase their und</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">erstanding of how and why cyclists behave the way the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">y</span><span